    <section id="nutrition">
        <h2>Nutrition</h2>
        <p>Mangoes are a delicious tropical fruit that are packed with vitamins, minerals, and antioxidants. Here's a breakdown of the nutritional content per 100 grams of fresh mango:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Calories: 60</li>
            <li>Carbohydrates: 15 g</li>
            <li>Sugars: 14 g</li>
            <li>Dietary Fiber: 1.6 g</li>
            <li>Protein: 0.8 g</li>
            <li>Fat: 0.4 g</li>
            <li>Vitamin C: 36.4 mg (60% of the Daily Value)</li>
            <li>Vitamin A: 54 µg (6% of the Daily Value)</li>
            <li>Folate: 43 µg (11% of the Daily Value)</li>
            <li>Vitamin E: 0.9 mg (5% of the Daily Value)</li>
            <li>Vitamin K: 4.2 µg (5% of the Daily Value)</li>
            <li>Potassium: 168 mg (5% of the Daily Value)</li>
            <li>Magnesium: 10 mg (3% of the Daily Value)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="intake">
        <h2>Recommended Intake</h2>
        <p>While mangoes are nutritious, it's important to consume them in moderation due to their natural sugar content. Here are some general guidelines for mango consumption:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>**Adults**: One to two cups of mango per day is a healthy amount.</li>
            <li>**Children**: One cup of mango per day is generally sufficient.</li>
            <li>**Individuals with diabetes**: Should monitor their mango intake carefully due to the fruit's sugar content.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>It's always best to consult with a healthcare provider or nutritionist to determine the right amount for your specific dietary needs.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="benefits">
        <h2>Health Benefits</h2>
        <p>Mangoes offer numerous health benefits, including:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>**Boosting Immunity**: High in vitamin C, mangoes help strengthen the immune system.</li>
            <li>**Supporting Eye Health**: Contains vitamin A and beta-carotene, which promote good vision.</li>
            <li>**Aiding Digestion**: Dietary fiber in mangoes aids in digestion and prevents constipation.</li>
            <li>**Promoting Skin Health**: Antioxidants in mangoes help protect and rejuvenate the skin.</li>
            <li>**Anti-inflammatory Properties**: Mangoes have anti-inflammatory compounds that may help reduce inflammation in the body.</li>
            <li>**Supporting Heart Health**: Contains potassium and magnesium, which are essential for maintaining a healthy heart.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section id="interesting-facts">
        <h2>Interesting Facts</h2>
        <p>Here are some fun and interesting facts about mangoes:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Mangoes are known as the "king of fruits" in many parts of the world.</li>
            <li>There are over 500 varieties of mangoes grown around the world.</li>
            <li>Mangoes originated in South Asia and have been cultivated for over 4,000 years.</li>
            <li>India is the largest producer of mangoes, accounting for nearly half of the world's production.</li>
            <li>Mangoes belong to the same family as pistachios and cashews.</li>
            <li>The mango tree can grow as tall as 100 feet and live for over 300 years.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

